[Donkey Kong Jr. Math](/Donkey_Kong_Jr._Math) is a rather infamous 1983 [edutainment](/Edutainment) [platform](/Platform_game) [video game](/Video_game) that emerged from the unlikely partnership of developer and publisher [Nintendo](/Nintendo) for their groundbreaking [Nintendo Entertainment System](/Nintendo_Entertainment_System). Conceived as a rather uninspired [spin-off](/Spin-off_(media)) of the immensely popular 1982 arcade hit [Donkey Kong Jr.](/Donkey_Kong_Jr.), the game attempted to fuse rudimentary arithmetic with platforming mechanics. In this educational endeavor, players were tasked with controlling the titular character, [Donkey Kong Jr.](/Donkey_Kong_Jr._(character)), as he navigated environments to solve simple math problems meticulously "set up" by his father, the original [Donkey Kong](/Donkey_Kong_(character)). One can only imagine the intellectual rigor involved.

Despite its prominent lineage, *Donkey Kong Jr. Math* stands out as the *only* game released in the Education Series of NES games in North America, a solitary distinction largely owing to its profound lack of commercial and critical success. Its limited appeal meant that Nintendo wisely chose not to expand the series. Nevertheless, the game has resurfaced periodically in various digital incarnations, a persistent ghost of Nintendo's past. It was made available as a playable unlockable within the 2002 [GameCube](/GameCube) video game [Animal Crossing](/Animal_Crossing_(video_game)) and subsequently offered on the [Virtual Console](/Virtual_Console) services for both the [Wii](/Wii) (in 2007) and the [Wii U](/Wii_U) (in 2014). In 2024, it was once again re-released for the [Nintendo Classics](/Nintendo_Classics) service, seemingly unable to escape its own digital afterlife. From its initial release, *Donkey Kong Jr. Math* was a resounding critical and commercial failure. It garnered widespread condemnation from numerous publications, including the staff at [IGN](/IGN), who, with characteristic bluntness, labeled it as one of the absolute worst titles ever to grace the Virtual Console platform. A truly uninspired attempt to make mathematics "fun," proving that some concepts are best left to their inherent elegance, rather than being subjected to pixelated distractions. ( [Full article...](/Donkey_Kong_Jr._Math) )

